oai_dc:dc.dc:title: "DOUBLE U BLOCK" AND "IBLOCK" - THE ARMOUR BLOCKS OF TWO NEW TYPES
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Twu, S.W.
Lin, S.C.
Chang, S.G.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: armor blocks
Double U block
Iblock
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A total of eleven new types of blocks are developed for this project. After performing a series of model tests for them and having a consideration of easy casting, two types of blocks are selected and presented here in this paper. They are named "Double U block" and "I block", respectively. The two have been compared with several existing types which have been widely used in Taiwan. It is shown that the Double U block is an excellent type of block with high stability and low reflection coefficient. The I block has an advantage of easy casting, although it is not outstanding in other characteristics.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 21 (1988): Proceedings of 21st Conference on Coastal Engineering, Torremolinos, Spain, 1988.; 175
